7. e-sir₂ gun₃-a dib-ba-ŋu₁₀-ne
#lem: esir[street]; gunu[speckled]; dib[pass]
#etcsl: line-id=7

8. gi gam-ma [...] X X X he₂-me-en#
#lem: gi[reed]; gurum[bend]; X; X; X; X; me[be]
#etcsl: line-id=8

9. še ab-sin₂-na# [...] sag₉#-ga he₂-me-en
#lem: še[barley]; absin[furrow]; X; sag[good]; me[be]
#etcsl: line-id=9

10. {d}ezina₂ [...] sag₉-ge he₂-me-en
#lem: Ezina[1]DN; X; sag[good]; me[be]
#etcsl: line-id=10

11. šag₄-tur₃ ama gan#-bi he₂-me-en!(EŠ)
#lem: šagtur[womb]; ama[mother]; gan[child-bearing]; me[be]
#etcsl: line-id=11

12. ama-za NE-KA {ŋiš}ŋeštin he₂-me-en
#lem: ama[mother]; X; ŋeštin[vine]; me[be]
#etcsl: line-id=12

13. (1:ki-ig-ga aŋ₂-ŋu₁₀#:1) diŋir-za NE-KA (2:nam-nun-e ak-a:2)
#lem: ki[place]; aŋ[measure]; diŋir[deity]; X; namnun[magnificence]; ak[do]
#etcsl: line-id=13

:13v.1.1: (#note: 1 ms. has instead:#) [...]-zu
#lem: X
:13v.2.1: (#note: 1 ms. has instead:#) nam-lu₂-ulu₃ i₃-ak
#lem: namlulu[humanity]; ak[do]

14. %e i₃-ma-al i₃-ma#-al %s (1:nam-zu he₂-a:1)
#lem: mal[be]V/i; mal[be]V/i; nam[fate]; me[be]
#etcsl: line-id=14

:14v.1.1: (#note: 1 ms. has instead:#) ka silim de₂-a
#lem: kag[mouth]; silim[healthy]; de[pour]

15. %e nu-ma-al %s niŋ₂-gig-zu he₂-a
#lem: mal[be]V/i; niŋgig[that which is bad]; me[be]
#etcsl: line-id=15

16. e₂ %e i₃-ma-al-[la] %s lu₂-bi he₂-me-en
#lem: e[house]; mal[be]V/i; lu[person]; me[be]
#etcsl: line-id=16

17. nin₉# sag₉#-ga ban₃-da sag₉-ga
